* Trump=E2=80=99s federal
agency overreach may backfire: This week, Elon Musk threw his weight behind=
 a proposal to merge the antitrust units of the Department of Justice and F=
ederal Trade Commission, essentially fulfilling a prophecy I made on Puck=
=E2=80=99s The Powers That Be podcast ( https://puck.news/podcast_episode/t=
rumps-enemy-within/?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing%2B+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283=
%2F4%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing%2B+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283%2F4%2F2=
5%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617=
da42abd12a ) after the election. If this actually happens, alongside Donald=
 Trump=E2=80=99s broader
push to curb the independence of agencies like the F.T.C. and F.C.C., the W=
hite House would gain even more direct influence over proposed mergers and =
acquisitions.

However, if that=E2=80=99s actually the objective, the consolidation may ha=
ve unintended consequences, potentially opening up a new defense strategy f=
or companies facing government antitrust challenges. Namely, companies may =
soon be on firmer legal ground to accuse regulators of =E2=80=9Cimproper se=
lective enforcement.=E2=80=9D AT&T and Time Warner
flirted with this defense in 2018=E2=80=94suspecting their merger was targe=
ted because of Trump=E2=80=99s disdain for CNN=E2=80=94but ended up not pur=
suing it at trial when the federal judge overseeing the case blocked their =
request to obtain White House=E2=80=93D.O.J. communications. The judge didn=
=E2=80=99t see enough evidence that the merger was indeed being singled out=
 to justify such a request.

But does the calculation change when a president exerts more direct control=
 over antitrust enforcement? I think so. After
all, the independence of various executive branch agencies was deliberately=
 strengthened after Watergate, amid concerns that political bias could tain=
t law enforcement. So here=E2=80=99s another prediction: We=E2=80=99re goin=
g to see legal battles over White House communications, as the Trump admini=
stration finds itself on shakier ground when it comes to shielding internal=
 discussions about corporate dealmaking. Trump might be busy at the moment =
kicking reporters out of their chairs, but the real question is
whether he=E2=80=99s also making it harder to keep things hidden.
* Will A.I. be Superman=E2=80=99s new kryptonite?: In the battle over wheth=
er Warner Bros. has lost certain foreign rights to Superman, perpetual Warn=
ers nemesis Marc Toberoff wants an injunction that would block the studio f=
rom exploiting the franchise=E2=80=94including James Gunn=E2=80=99s upcomin=
g reboot this July=E2=80=94in Canada, the U.K., Ireland, and Australia. Thi=
s is a
long shot, as I wrote ( https://puck.news/new-superman-could-be-barred-from=
-release-outside-u-s/?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing%2B+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2=
